  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (f523139 2022-11-16T00:07:04.576471Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\neth_getStorageAt\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nRunning `anvil --fork-url http://192.168.0.xxx:8545` I'm able to make successful eth_call requests to past block numbers but eth_getStorageAt returns this error: `BlockOutOfRangeError: block height is 15985163 but requested was 15950000`\r\n\r\nError comes from https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/cbf77c251f9bab770ab0114bd6bda6f47049b388/anvil/src/eth/backend/mem/mod.rs#L1333\r\n\r\nTrace logs\r\n```\r\n2022-11-16T21:08:39.156324Z DEBUG request{method=POST uri=/ version=HTTP/1.1}: tower_http::trace::on_request: started processing request\r\n2022-11-16T21:08:39.156365Z TRACE request{method=POST uri=/ version=HTTP/1.1}: rpc: handling call id=Number(11) method=\"eth_getStorageAt\"\r\n2022-11-16T21:08:39.156369Z TRACE request{method=POST uri=/ version=HTTP/1.1}: rpc: received method call id=Number(11) method=\"eth_getStorageAt\"\r\n2022-11-16T21:08:39.156376Z TRACE request{method=POST uri=/ version=HTTP/1.1}: rpc::api: executing eth request\r\n2022-11-16T21:08:39.156405Z  INFO request{method=POST uri=/ version=HTTP/1.1}: node::user: eth_getStorageAt\r\n2022-11-16T21:08:39.156409Z  WARN request{method=POST uri=/ version=HTTP/1.1}: backend: Not historic state found for block=15950000\r\n2022-11-16T21:08:39.156424Z DEBUG request{method=POST uri=/ version=HTTP/1.1}: tower_http::trace::on_response: finished processing request latency=0 ms status=200\r\n2022-11-16T21:08:39.156430Z TRACE encode_headers: hyper::proto::h1::role: Server::encode status=200, body=Some(Known(135)), req_method=Some(POST)\r\n```\r\n\r\nSeems like it's only trying to use local history rather than passing the request through to the fork, so maybe this is just not implemented yet rather than bug",
